hits.title: What are AI agents? Definition, examples, and types
hits.snippet: Learn whatAIagentsare, how they work, and what types ofagentsexist.AIagentsare software systems that useAIto pursue goals and complete tasks on behalf of users, with reasoning, planning, and autonomy.

hits.title: A Beginner's Guide To Building AI Agents - Forbes
hits.snippet: This beginner's guide explains whatAIagentsare, how they differ from traditional automation and chatbots, and why they are becoming essential for businesses.

hits.title: What are AI agents? - IBM
hits.snippet: What areAIagents? An artificial intelligence (AI)agentis a system that autonomously performs tasks by designing workflows with available tools.AIagentscan encompass a wide range of functions beyond natural language processing including decision-making, problem-solving, interacting with external environments and performing actions.

hits.title: How Do AI Agents Work? AI Explained | Microsoft Copilot
hits.snippet: Learn howAIagentswork, support task automation, and boost efficiency in business workflows. See real-world examples in action.

hits.title: What are AI Agents?- Agents in Artificial Intelligence Explained - AWS
hits.snippet: What areAIAgents? An artificial intelligence (AI)agentis a software program that can interact with its environment, collect data, and use that data to perform self-directed tasks that meet predetermined goals. Humans set goals, but anAIagentindependently chooses the best actions it needs to perform to achieve those goals.
